page.title: 13CHURCH IN WICK ST. LAWRENCE
page.content: Both Wick St. Lawrence and Kingston Seymour have parish churches,but neither now have their own vicar.Kingston Seymour is part of the ecclesiastical parish of Yatton and Yeo Moor with Yatton and Kenn.Wick St. Lawrence is part of the parish of Kewstoke.The church is dedicated to St. Lawrence. Wick St. Lawrence church is a very old foundation with a large and full churchyard.The church itself is perpendicular in style and was very much restored in the 1860's.The church and churchyard are beautifully maintained and there is one service on a Sunday and one mid_week.The non_ conformist chapel is now closed and has been converted into a private house.All members of denominations need to go outside the village for a place of worship.
